Inspector-General of Police (IGP) Mohammed Adamu has approved the promotion of 4,134 traffic warden officers to their next ranks. The promotion includes 65 officers who were elevated to the rank of a Deputy Superintendent of Traffic; 245 Officers to Assistant Superintendent of Traffic II; 138 Officers to Senior Traffic Warden; 3,683 Men to Grade I and three Men from Grade III to Grade II. Force spokesman Frank Mba, a Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP), announced the promotion in a statement on Thursday in Abuja. “The IGP notes that the promotion of the officers is part of the ongoing efforts by the Force to ensure that deserving personnel are promoted accordingly, to encourage hard work and further entrench the culture of merit, excellence and dedication to duties,” the state said.